                  "VDGT"
                ],
                "institute": "1USAOHO"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Experiment was performed using the 4.5",
                "MV Tandem Pelletron electrostatic accelerator at Ohio",
                "University."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Two targets were used simultaneously a graphite and a",
                "CH2 plastic target."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SI",
                "SILI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A proton telescope consisting of a",
                "300 mu-m thick, 150 mm2 ion implanted silicon dE",
                "detector and a 5000 mu-m thick, 200 mm2 drifted-",
                "lithium silicon E detector was used to detect recoil",
                "protons from CH2 target to determine the neutron flux."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "NAICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Three pairs of 7.62-cm diameter by 7.62-cm",
                "thick NaI detectors were used to measure positron",
                "annihilation gamma rays from 11C decays. Pairs of",
                "detectors and the graphite targets were held with",
                "their axes aligned inside almost equal diameter",
                "acrylic tubes. CH2 target, graphite target and",
                "graphite shields were mesured simultaneously after",
                "irradiation."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The polyethylene target also acted",
                "simultaneously as the converter for the recoil proton",
                "telescope. Special care was taken for exact geometrical",
                "alignement of all components, beam, Ti neutron",
                "producing target, CH2 and graphite targets and",
                "proton telescope."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "D-T"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Deuterons were accelerated to energies between",
                "3.1 and 9.1 MeV and allowed to strike a 472.86 GBq",
                "tritium target. Deuteron beam currents were typically",
                "between 0.8 and 1.0 mu-A. The tritium was deposited",
                "as titanium tritide on a 49-mm diameter 1-mm thick",
                "OFHC copper substrate at a density of about 2000",
                "mu-g/cm2 over a circular active area of 30-mm diameter."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Cross section was determined from the analysis of the",
                "11B growth curves from decay of 11C for coincidence",
                "and singles measurements.",
                "At the energy of 24.7 MeV two independent measurements",
                "were made with slightly different results. Both data",
                "at 24.69 MeV(graphite terget) and 24.74 (polyethylene",
                "target) are compiled."
              ]
            }
          ],
